Why Choose Bonded Nylon TKT 40?

Known for its high tensile strength, resistance to abrasion, and smooth performance, Bonded Nylon TKT 40 is trusted by professionals in upholstery, leathercraft, and industrial sewing.

Profix Heavy-Duty Spray Adhesive (500ml)
Short description:
PROFIX Heavy Duty Spray Adhesive

PROFIX Heavy Duty Spray Adhesive is a high-strength, fast-drying aerosol adhesive designed for demanding applications. Its advanced formulation ensures a powerful bond, making it ideal for use across multiple industries, including furniture, flooring, and automotive sectors.

Key Features:

  • Latest Formulation: Engineered for maximum adhesion and durability.
  • High Strength Adhesive: Provides exceptional bonding power for a wide range of surfaces.
  • Fast & Efficient: Quick-drying formula for professional results.
  • Easy to Use: Applies directly from the can with a variable spray pattern.

Directions for Use:

  1. Ensure surfaces are clean, dry, and free from dirt.
  2. For a strong bond, apply multiple light coats to both surfaces; for a lighter bond, apply to only one surface.
  3. Allow a few moments for solvents to evaporate.
  4. Press surfaces together firmly, working outward to ensure a secure bond.
  5. After use, invert the can and spray for a few seconds to clear the nozzle.

Applications:

PROFIX is ideal for bonding foam to a variety of surfaces, making it perfect for the furniture, flooring, and automotive industries. It is also widely used in packaging, laminating, and decorative trades. Additionally, it can be applied to soundproofing and containment areas for asbestos removal.

Recommended Uses:

  • Foam
  • Rubber
  • Cardboard & Paper
  • Fabrics (including carpet backing)
  • Wood & Plastic (Not suitable for heavily plasticised PVC)

Safety & Precautions:

  • Highly Flammable: Keep away from heat, sparks, and open flames.
  • Health Risk: Contains Dichloromethane – suspected of causing cancer.
  • Keep out of reach of children.
  • Wear protective gloves, clothing, and eye protection.
  • Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local regulations.
  • Do not puncture or burn the can, even after use.
  • Store away from direct sunlight and temperatures above 50°C (122°F).

Important Note:

Not suitable for heavily plasticised PVC. It is recommended to evaluate the adhesive in application conditions before commercial use.
